rComments: She is easy going and passionate about what she taught.

Tatiana is amazing! I took"Literature and Painting in Russia and the West" and fell in love with Russian literature. We went on a field trip to the AGO which was fun and educational. She shows real interest in her students and offers constructive feedback on papers. She cares, which makes you care as well. Great class, highly recommend

A great professor, I am far from being a literature student, and took "Literature and Painting in Russia and the West" on a whim for elective credits.  Professor Smolyarova assigned great readings that were relevant, spurred really interesting discussion, and otherwise made me actually like literature.  Expect to be forced to participate.
